A 29-year-old taxi driver was arrested on Friday, 9 July on N3 highway near Harrismith for possession of Khat plant drugs. The police were doing normal roadblock on N3 when they stopped a white Quantum taxi with a GP registration number, which was travelling from Joburg to Durban. Police spokeswoman Colonel Thandi Mbambo said during the search, officers saw three sealed boxes. “They enquired from the driver who alleged that the boxes were given to him by someone in Joburg to deliver in Durban,” she said When the police opened the boxes, they found that they contained 327 bundles of Khat plants and 5kg Khat plant drugs worth an estimated street value of R327 000. The suspect is expected to appear in the Harrismith Magistrates Court on Monday, 12 July.